 # LinkedIn Banner Generator
 
-A lightweight web tool to create a **professional LinkedIn banner (1584 × 396 px)** for tech and AI-focused profiles.
+A simple web tool to create a clean, professional LinkedIn banner (1584 × 396 px), mainly aimed at tech/AI profiles.
+
+I built this to avoid using design tools every time I needed a decent-looking banner — it just generates one directly in the browser using HTML/CSS.
 
-Built using **pure HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and inline SVG** — no frameworks or external dependencies.
+No frameworks, no setup. Just open the file and tweak it.
 
 ---
 
-## Overview
+## What it does
 
-This project generates a modern, dark-themed LinkedIn banner featuring a clean tech aesthetic with subtle visual elements like neural network graphics, skill highlights, and dual image placeholders.
+It generates a dark-themed banner with a modern “tech” look — subtle background visuals, skill highlights, and space for two images.
 
-It is designed to help developers quickly create a strong personal branding banner without using design tools.
+The layout is fixed to LinkedIn’s banner size, so you don’t have to worry about resizing or alignment.
 
 ---
 
 ## Features
 
-* Dark-themed professional layout with blue accent styling
-* Inline SVG-based neural network illustration
-* Code-style watermark using JetBrains Mono
-* Dual image slots with smooth blending and grayscale effects
-* Skill badges with clear visual hierarchy (primary & secondary)
-* Fully responsive scaling using vanilla JavaScript
-* Uses Google Fonts (Inter + JetBrains Mono)
+* Dark theme with a blue accent (easy to change)
+* Inline SVG-based background (neural network style)
+* Code-like watermark for a subtle dev vibe
+* Two image slots with blending + grayscale effects
+* Skill badges with a simple hierarchy
+* Works directly in the browser (no build step)
+* Uses Inter + JetBrains Mono fonts
 
